Codex doesn't have a per-project memory system the way Claude
Code does, but AGENTS.md already serves a similar role. This
prompt is a no-op except as a reminder to confirm AGENTS.md is
loaded.

If you'd like persistent reminders across sessions, edit
`AGENTS.md` directly — Codex reads it at session start. The
gofasta-installed AGENTS.md already contains the "First 60
seconds" orientation, layer rule, must-NOT-do list, and self-check
guidance.
